<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> that’s what you say • you said it</xh5><p> <i>that’s what you say</i>—(also: says you) is used to show one’s disagreement or scorn of the other speaker’s opinion: “They aren’t going to go to the police.” “<u>That’s what you say</u>.”</p><p> <i>you said it</i>—(also: you can say that again) is used to show strong agreement with what another person has just said: “That sure was a good show.” “<u>You said it</u>!”</p> </entry>
